All Classes

Class Description
Airport
The class which represent an Airport object and all the important available data about it.
AirportInfoPlugin
The AirportInfoPlugin class is the class that gathers data about the airports available in the .csv "database" file and shows it to the user.
APTCategory
APTCategory enum class classifies the size of the airport.
CreateFlightPlanPlugin
The CreateFlightPlanPlugin class is the class that uses both AirportInfoPlugin and WeatherInfoPlugin on top of which uses the waypoints database in order to create the route plan between two specified airports.
DialogCenter
The DialogCenter class provides the communication interface between the program and its user.
Downloader
The Downloader class is responsible for the download preparation and the METAR information download itself from the provider website.
ExitFlightPlannerPlugin
The ExitFlightPlannerPlugin represents a class which handles the application exiting after the confirmation of the user.
FilesHandler
The class which is responsible for files handling and creating, path computing and searching the required resources for correct program execution.
FlightPlanner
The entry point to the program.
METARDecoder
The METARProcessor is the class responsible for parsing, modifying and processing the file(s) with METAR entries.
NotNull
Custom NotNull annotation which helps to indicate that a non-null value has to be passed as parameter, returned from a method etc...
Nullable
Custom Nullable annotation which helps to indicate that a null value may possibly be passed as a method parameter, returned from a method etc...
Plugin
Plugin interface represents an independent part of the program performing its own Plugin.action().
Runway
The class which represents a Runway object of the specified airport for better understanding of its components.
Utilities
The class which provides different useful methods used in the different parts of the program.
WeatherInfoPlugin
The WeatherInfoPlugin class is responsible for gathering data and creating the output text concerning the weather at specified airport(s).
